In this free 75-minute online class, actors read and perform monologues for feedback (or just watch), and I cover a lot about choosing monologues, including 

‚Ä¢ How to find material that‚Äôs great for you

‚Ä¢ Where to look

‚Ä¢ How to recognize good material

‚Ä¢ Choosing well for specific kinds of auditions

‚Ä¢ Building a killer repertoire

‚Ä¢ Effective cutting and editing

‚Ä¢ When and when not to do overdone monologues

‚Ä¢ The ‚ÄúHello, This Is Me‚Äù monologue and why it‚Äôs so incredibly valuable for auditioning actors

SUNDAY OCTOBER 5 | 12noon‚Äî1:15pm Eastern

RESERVE | classes@monologueaudition.com

Can‚Äôt do this one? Email classes@monologueaudition.com to join my list and hear about upcoming classes and free events

KAREN KOHLHAAS is an Atlantic Theater Company director, teacher and founding member. She was voted Best NYC Monologue Teacher and Best NYC Cold Reading teacher by Backstage readers. Her book THE MONOLOGUE AUDITION is recommended by Helen Mirren in her Master Class on Acting.

items.text:
Casting Call

We are looking for actors to make an example scene for the film pitch, with which we are looking for to ask for funding for the feature length low-budget independent film based on a real story, hidden truths and mystic experiences, mixed with fantasy.

The action of the example scene develops, as a guy (20-26 years old) confronts with two young men (26-35 years old), who ask him to give back them money, that a young man borrowed from them for the business, that failed. They are warning him with death and preparing to hit him until death, but accidentally something happens as a hand of help.

It's going be around 3h of filming for one day: 14th of October day time in Croydon, London, next to Waddon station. 

Salary will be ¬£25 for the actor after filming, plus if actor will agree to act in the next, but real film shootings, then agreed compensation of percent of how much the film will earn after distribution.

Acting experience is not necessary, but preferable and being comfortable in front of camera with a wish to act.

Actors:
A young guy with blonde colour hair (20-26 years old)

A young man number 1 with black or brown hair  (26-35 years old)

A young man number 2 with black or brown hair (26-35 years old)

If you are interested, write me:

I am producer and one of the directors of the film. My name: Ieva Kondrataviciute 
Email: ieva.kristina.kondrataviciute@gmail.com
Contact WhatsApp: +44 7548710376

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 1st week in November 2025 (date tbc)

Summary: Set in the backroom of a dive bar. A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer. Black African, 25-35, Nigerian accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£500 for 20 hours (rehearsals & shoot).

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European, 25-35, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg, powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

You will need professional experience playing roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
Film crews are using Photoshop IDs and hand over cash envelopes to get paid?

Saturation's co-founders Jens Jacob & Simon Tam break down why film production financial tools haven't evolved like Figma, Frame.io, and Airtable did for their industries and how they're building the solution. From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

CEO | Director | Editor | Producer

I began my career as an editor and animator, contributing to numerous TV commercials, documentaries, and films. With a passion for storytelling and visual craft, I transitioned into film direction‚Äîleading diverse projects ranging from high-end TVCs and impactful documentaries to feature films. Over the years, I've developed a deep understanding of media production from concept to completion.

Now, I'm proud to launch my own production company‚Äîoffering full-spectrum media services under one roof. From creative development to final delivery, we‚Äôre committed to producing powerful, original content that resonates across platforms and audiences.

www.deepriversfilms.com

**Casting for: East Asian actors, all types, all ages**

Holding open auditions for Asian actors, men and women, for a number of Asian film and episodic projects (action, thriller, drama, rom-com) we are working on.

East Asian ethnicity, looking for early 20's look (for group 1) and all ages (for group 2). Non-union. Payment status depends on the project.

Auditions are Friday, Saturday, Sunday, October 10th, 11th, 12th in East Vancouver studio. You will perform a short set of sides and then do a monologue of your choice.

Shooting will be throughout Fall and Winter 2025/2026.

If interested, please email castingproject604@gmail.comNOSPAM (remove 'NOSPAM') with your photos, resume with a cover letter about your experience or any training you have had and your availability for the three dates.

Shortlisted talent will be asked to audition.

Thank you for your attention.

We are seeking enthusiastic actresses for an upcoming independent zombie movie. This project blends horror, suspense, and dark humor. Shooting dates are TBD and will take place in the local area.

Who we are looking for? 

Women aged 16-28 who have a passion for horror! We have leading roles that need to be filled and want young up and coming talent to take that spotlight! 

WE ARE SEARCHING FOR TONS OF NEW TALENT AND ENCOURAGE ALL WOMAN OF ALL BACKGROUNDS TO APPLY. WE DEDICATE OUR PROCESS INTO INVOLVING AND UPLIFITING THOSE WHO MAY FACE BARRIERS. (If you need accommodations please let us know)

To be considered, please leave your contact info in the link below and our team will be in contact shortly. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScVk2oj-ptgpQGc2fkTnoIsQNqpjmvULZ5VqiLGJStwHGN3rQ/viewform?fbclid=IwQ0xDSwKd7RFleHRuA2FlbQIxMQABHm_-bBN6sRA6a7BHOaFJxrigOEUykOBehWrZ6bIpMHvlcUu6F8Uf4bF1DUIU_aem_cMRRZUQ6WYUZMnP7j7yodA

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

CASTING CALL 

Self Tapes Wanted for University of Colorado Denver Senior Thesis Project

In-Person Callbacks in early October

TITLE: *Action! 1987*

PROJECT TYPE: Short Film (Student, Non-Union)

LOCATION: Denver Metro Area

TIMEFRAME: 2 Days of Shooting in late October 

SYNOPSIS: In 1987, a young woman, Luda, leaves a movie theatre with her cinephile boyfriend Julian. They argue about the morality of the action heroes they see on screen. Luda says the so-called ‚Äúgood guys‚Äù are always doing bad things. Julian thinks it‚Äôs more complicated than that.

The next day at work while helping with a children‚Äôs beauty pageant, Luda finds that right and wrong aren‚Äôt always so black and white when the parents of a young girl, Angie, leaves her alone in front of Luda. That night Luda and Julian walk into the movie theatre and she is shocked to see herself up on the silver screen.

COMPENSATION (Non-Union) : Reel, Food, Gas, Undying Appreciation

ROLE: 

Dad (Male, Late 30‚Äôs - Late 40‚Äôs): An stern and demanding pageant Dad with a wandering eye.

Please send your headshot/resume/other materials to [MARLEY.TREMMEL@UCDENVER.EDU](mailto:MARLEY.TREMMEL@UCDENVER.EDU) to receive sides and further instructions for submitting a self-tape. Thank you!

**CASTING CALL - Featured Extras and Background**

**Title:** CrimeCast (Episode 01A)

**Genre:** Dark Comedy, Crime Mystery, Episodic 

**Logline:** Emotionally unstable True Crime podcast host wants answers, but has to decide which is more important: her friends' and family's safety or the truth of what happened to her dead best friend.

**Roles:**

**Featured Extras and Background:**

**We are seeking a diverse group of individuals to fill approximately 10 featured extra and background roles.**

**Contact info: If you are interested and available, please send a selfie or headshot along with your height to **[crimecast22@gmail.com](mailto:crimecast22@gmail.com) **and** [phyllisramie@gmail.com](mailto:phyllisramie@gmail.com)

**Director:** Phyllis Ramie Groves

**Director of Photography:** Xavier Leonard

**Production Type:** Student Film (Prod 3)

**Compensation:** Unpaid. Food, Footage, and Credit.

**Shooting Date and Location:** October 15th in Castle Rock, CO. Carpooling from CCA may be available.

‚Ä¢ All other roles unpaid (meals + IMDb credit provided)

(PLEASE BE AWARE WE ARE CASTING FOR MULTIPLE VENUES SO READ CAREFULLY & APPLY ACCORDINGLY)

items.text:
Casting Call

We are looking for actors to make an example scene for the film pitch, with which we are looking for to ask for funding for the feature length low-budget independent film based on a real story, hidden truths and mystic experiences, mixed with fantasy.

The action of the example scene develops, as a guy (20-26 years old) confronts with two young men (26-35 years old), who ask him to give back them money, that a young man borrowed from them for the business, that failed. They are warning him with death and preparing to hit him until death, but accidentally something happens as a hand of help.

It's going be around 3h of filming for one day: 14th of October day time and salary will be ¬£25 for the actor after filming, plus if actor will agree to act in the next, but real film shootings, then agreed compensation of percent of how much the film will earn after distribution.

Acting experience is not necessary, but preferable and being comfortable in front of camera with a wish to act.

Actors:
A young guy with blonde colour hair (20-26 years old)

A young man number 1 with black or brown hair  (26-35 years old)

A young man number 2 with black or brown hair (26-35 years old)

If you are interested, write me: ieva.kristina.kondrataviciute@gmail.com

topComments.text: Interested

items.text:
PIGE MED PROTESE S√òGES TIL KORTFILM - (L√òNNET) -√ÖRHUS

Til kortfilmen ‚ÄúDukkebarn‚Äù s√∏ger vi en pige med en ben protese eller arm protese til rollen som AURA. 

Lidt om filmen: 
‚ÄúDukkebarn udforsker den skr√∏belige gr√¶nse mellem fantasi og virkelighed gennem √∏jnene p√• Aura. Hendes fascination til dukker bliver en m√•de at bearbejde hendes egen smertelige virkelighed og hendes forhold til sin krop. Gennem leg, skabelse og destruktion konfronteres hun med sine dybeste frugter og l√¶ngsler. 

Alder: I mellem 6-12 √•r. 

Vi filmer i √Örhus d. 16-18 Januar 2026. Jobbet vil v√¶re l√∏nnet, samt forplejning og transport. S√∏g gerne lige meget hvor i landet du bor. Vi ser gerne s√• mange som muligt;) 

Skriv til @Rirh.prod@gmail.com med emnet ‚ÄúCASTING -DUKKEBARN‚Äù. Skrive gerne lidt om dig selv, samt er billede og evt erfaring. 

Hvis du er g√•et videre til casting, eller f√•et rollen vil du f√• svar inden 10 Januar. 

Jeg gl√¶der mig til at h√∏re fra jer. 

Mvh Rebecca Renner Hansen - Dukkebarn film

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

Til den ambiti√∏se og absurd-komiske kortfilm FLYT DIG, leder vi lige nu efter en r√¶kke skuespillere. 

**LOGLINE**

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske f√¶tter hj√¶lper ham med at flytte, m√• han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud ‚Äì men om at turde definere sine egne gr√¶nser.

**ADAM **(hovedrolle, omkring 18)
* Ung af udseende
* Stille, meget almindelig, ikke s√¶rlig bem√¶rkelsesv√¶rdig
* har sv√¶rt ved at s√¶tte gr√¶nser

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 1**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 2**

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 3**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 4**
* BIROLLER, ALLE mellem 40-80 √•r
* ALLE familiemedlemmer har replikker
* K√òN/UDSEENDE er underordnet 

**ROOMIE 1**

**ROOMIE 2**

**ROOMIE 3**
* BIROLLER, DRENGE mellem 17-22
* ALLE roomies har replikker 
* UDSEENDE er underordnet

Optagelserne kommer til at ligge i Aarhus, omkring datoerne 14-15-16 oktober. Da dette er i samarbejde med Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, er rollerne ul√∏nnet.

Hvis man er interesseret i en/flere af rollerne, bedes man sende en mail p√• sara774g@gmail.som med alder og eventuel erfaring/showreel.

Vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra jer!

Vh 

Sara Riahi, Freya Carlsen & Sylvester Byder

items.text:
Heyyy! I‚Äôm Anne Musisi and I‚Äôm an actor, director, and career development coach with a mission to help creatives and actors thrive. Drawing on decades of experience in global theatre, screen, and coaching, I‚Äôve created a wellbeing tool designed specifically for actors and creatives. My mission is to help you overcome self-doubt, reconnect with your creative core, and build a sustainable, fulfilling career.

It is also a tool that can be used by therapists, coaches and facilitators to spark deeper conversations and even provide a thematic structure for your workshops. 

My work merges creative practice with personal growth and career strategy. This tool is the practical embodiment of my belief: that when creatives nurture their inner life, their art and profession flourish too.

If you or anyone are interested in learning more, do feel free to DM. I‚Äôd love to chat more.
https://www.annemusisi.com

Heyyy! I‚Äôm Anne Musisi and I‚Äôm an actor, director, and career development coach with a mission to help creatives and actors thrive. Drawing on decades of experience in global theatre, screen, and coaching, I‚Äôve created a wellbeing tool designed specifically for actors and creatives. My mission is to help you overcome self-doubt, reconnect with your creative core, and build a sustainable, fulfilling career.

It is also a tool that can be used by therapists, coaches and facilitators to spark deeper conversations and even provide a thematic structure for your workshops. 

My work merges creative practice with personal growth and career strategy. This tool is the practical embodiment of my belief: that when creatives nurture their inner life, their art and profession flourish too.

If you or anyone are interested in learning more, do feel free to DM. I‚Äôd love to chat more.

**Autumn greetings to all our actors from Estonia and beyond!** üçÇüçÅ

All-level Meisner workshop taking place in Tallinn soon!

Join us, November 15‚Äì16th, for a two-day workshop with actor coach Dominic Kelly.

Whether you‚Äôre just starting out or looking to deepen your practice, this course offers a focused exploration of Sanford Meisner‚Äôs core exercises‚Äîhelping you access and express your most truthful impulses in response to your partner‚Äôs behavior.

You‚Äôll learn to:
 ‚ú® access your most truthful impulses
 ‚ú® connect deeply with your partner
 ‚ú® strengthen your instincts & emotional expression
 ‚ú® create freedom to be fully present, on stage and in life

This workshop is both a training ground and a safe space to challenge yourself, explore truth in performance, and deepen your connection to others and the imaginary world of a scene.

For our alumni, we have the option to work on a short, self-chosen scene on the second day (Let us know by email in advance if you would like to do this)

  üóì When: **15‚Äì16 November 2025 | 10:00‚Äì16:00**
  üìç Where: **Tallinn, Old Town**
  üë• For: Actors, performers, directors, writers, coaches‚Äîanyone curious about living & working more truthfully

Spots are limited, book yours in here:

We are seeking enthusiastic actresses for an upcoming independent zombie movie. This project blends horror, suspense, and dark humor. Shooting dates are TBD and will take place in the local area.

Who we are looking for? 

Women aged 16-28 who have a passion for horror! We have leading roles that need to be filled and want young up and coming talent to take that spotlight! 

WE ARE SEARCHING FOR TONS OF NEW TALENT AND ENCOURAGE ALL WOMAN OF ALL BACKGROUNDS TO APPLY. WE DEDICATE OUR PROCESS INTO INVOLVING AND UPLIFITING THOSE WHO MAY FACE BARRIERS. (If you need accommodations please let us know)

To be considered, please leave your contact info in the link below and our team will be in contact shortly. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScVk2oj-ptgpQGc2fkTnoIsQNqpjmvULZ5VqiLGJStwHGN3rQ/viewform?fbclid=IwQ0xDSwKd7RFleHRuA2FlbQIxMQABHm_-bBN6sRA6a7BHOaFJxrigOEUykOBehWrZ6bIpMHvlcUu6F8Uf4bF1DUIU_aem_cMRRZUQ6WYUZMnP7j7yodA

items.text:
CASTING CALL for a SHORT we are producing in November.

COLD FEET

A dark comedy --- On his wedding day, Thomas tries to weasel his way out of lifetime commitment. But the universe has other plans for him.

Casting for

Thomas - The groom. A go-with-the-flow guy who realises too late that getting married is not what he wants.

Elliott - The best man who tries to set his friend on the right path.

Jane - An intense bride, who refuses to see the ugly truth about the supposed love of her life.

Must be willing to travel to Beaconsfield, Buckinghamshire (HP9).

Filming dates tentatively set for November 29-30, 2025.

This is a paid opportunity. Short film rates.

Please fill out this form to register your interest! https://forms.gle/U8PgSfkotmqSa9M16

items.text:
Born and raised in Inglewood, California, I‚Äôve always carried a mix of grit, style, and vision. I started as a track athlete, sprinting at Long Beach State, but my journey has expanded beyond the lanes.

I‚Äôm stepping fully into modeling and acting and building a presence that merges discipline, athleticism, and storytelling. On camera, I bring the same intensity and focus that I‚Äôve always carried on the track.

My mission is bigger than looks or roles: I want to create art, shift culture, and open conversations about mental health, especially for men. Whether it‚Äôs through a campaign, a film, or a character, I aim to bring authenticity, energy, and impact to everything I touch.

items.text:
Hi! I am currently looking for an actor to cast in a role for my upcoming *unpaid* *nonunion* Kent State student film which will be filmed over four days from October 9‚Äì12 in Canton, OH. 

The actor needs only to be available during October 10th and 11th.

The film is about a headstrong young woman moves in with her belligerent partner, her once absent but perceptive father attempts to reconcile with her by providing enlightenment

The father is 50 (40 - 60 preferred age range) soft-spoken, understanding, and desperate for reconciliation with his daughter June.

If you‚Äôre interested, please contact me through the address below and I will provide you with the materials to audition. This is an urgent casting so serious inquiries only.

Looking forward to potentially working together!

cass.clsmith@gmail.com

JOIN US üé≠

The Diceplayers acting school is hosting a one-day writing workshop on November 22nd! We'll have a workshop with Kevin Curran, a Q&A session with Paul Howard, and a book signing! 

To book your spot, email diceplayers@gmail.com or phone 085 2550344 

The event runs from 10 AM to 6:30 PM, and lunch will be provided at a local cafe/restaurant. Don't miss out! #TheDiceplayers #ActingWorkshop #KevinCurran #PaulHoward #BookSigning #DublinEvents #writers #writing #creative

items.text:
We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals ‚Äì17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer ¬£700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

CASTING CALL FOR PLAY IN LONDON:

I'm casting four roles (3 female/ 1 male) for a showcase reading of my new play 'The Beat of the Bronzewing' at the Hen & Chickens Theatre in Islington, London on November 12th. 

The Beat of the Bronzewing was longlisted for the Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025 and focuses on three women in remote tropical Australia, desperate to turn their lives around yet paralysed by fear. It explores how their insecurities and the wild landscape magnify their loneliness and isolation, setting them on a course of self-destruction as they increasingly turn on each other. 

Apply via the Google Form link here: ([https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0](https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR5Hu3UGD1qZxdMIWR2d_80GBkptrNYjvmQKWCmydP--a9Hs-hLLyq9GDFqZlA_aem_Tn4v_Jq0QGNGHkakZGOTFw)). 

Know someone who might be interested? Please spread the word!

 

Important info:  

| Rehearsals on November 9th (10am-6pm) and November 12th (2:30-7pm)

| In-person auditions on October 8th (12-5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre in Angel, Islington following a selection (let us know if you need an alternative) 

| Volunteer opportunity - all actors will be given ¬£50 pounds for expenses

| Apply via Google Form link here: ([https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fd98EEgkgK0%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR6STL3lXt8cdBCGpSYrv5XvpSHW_IA3JoKT1r83vfoq93QMm80Vsj_31_s09Q_aem_cSh3Con8n2nt4AWPGVxuRQ&h=AT3UxWehtfMsSwB5REWXCX3UHOR-IbCtMgXw11AVLk6tzDWjrVusQvMal4tBpcgnFYk6zyQaOjGLupowpQG2C_2Lnir-BGUKBI9MH_CMk-pF1FA-OIIZsoxFFo2bSplp5WYnUXM019O0AA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3ZSFem3LQLGHpnYQQix_aB1OTC-II_z6ULdAtsi-abLh1hVZ6JVCHBA2u98UrsMqLeuH-VMmJqsPkp102wldtR3ternY9MXCYToG6v5AsMe_3MJvv4-JL2oxzyNfi1_K7uf8f1E10-EvfRY4j_OFAP6nnjb1-iHjbe3u5HTKwR)) - thank you!

CASTING CALL/ NON-UNION 

Casting Russian speaking roles in the short anti-war film 'During Winter, I Thought of My Father' written and directed by Danill Vasilyev. 

Please submit resume, headshot(s), and demo reel (if applicable) to duringwinter26@gmail.com to receive sides. 

Audition submission deadline: OCTOBER 18, 2025

Character descriptions below: 

ARTYOM

Russian speaking man, early 20s.

Description: Having seen the horrors of war firsthand, this young man became a conscientious objector who deserted the war. And despite paying a high price for his decision, losing a leg to frostbite, Artyom remains entrenched in his anti-war beliefs. A bright young

man from a middle-class family, who loves poetry and shoemaking, Artyom uses every ounce of his physical and mental might to get back to his family. 

VLADIMIR 

Russian speaking man, 50s-60s. 

A staunch patriot who was once a soldier too. A decorated one, whose pride in his heroic exploits for the Motherland could be felt from afar. But now, the old man stands alone. No family, no friends, no backing from the state which he holds so dear. His only son died

in a war years ago. All that‚Äôs left is the inextinguishable belief in his national identity, which has been built from years of tradition and pride. 

Rate: Unpaid, travel and food will be provided.

items.summary:
CASTING CALL/ NON-UNION 

Casting Russian speaking roles in the short anti-war film 'During Winter, I Thought of My Father' written and directed by Danill Vasilyev. 

Please submit resume, headshot(s), and demo reel (if applicable) to duringwinter26@gmail.com to receive sides. 

Audition submission deadline: OCTOBER 18, 2025

Character descriptions below: 

ARTYOM

Russian speaking man, early 20s.

Description: Having seen the horrors of war firsthand, this young man became a conscientious objector who deserted the war. And despite paying a high price for his decision, losing a leg to frostbite, Artyom remains entrenched in his anti-war beliefs. A bright young

man from a middle-class family, who loves poetry and shoemaking, Artyom uses every ounce of his physical and mental might to get back to his family. 

VLADIMIR 

Russian speaking man, 50s-60s. 

A staunch patriot who was once a soldier too. A decorated one, whose pride in his heroic exploits for the Motherland could be felt from afar. But now, the old man stands alone. No family, no friends, no backing from the state which he holds so dear. His only son died

in a war years ago. All that‚Äôs left is the inextinguishable belief in his national identity, which has been built from years of tradition and pride. 

Rate: Unpaid, travel and food will be provided.

**CASTINGCALL!!! (Ul√∏nnet)**

Hejsa. vi er i gang med vores andet projekt her p√• Potemkin, den jyske filmskole - Masterclass. Vi s√∏ger derfor skuespillere til Hovedrollen **Alfred**.

Logline: ‚Äú**Spildt M√¶lk**‚Äù I denne absurde coming-of-age komedie, om identitet, vaner og det at finde sig selv,  m√∏der vi Alfred en ung mand der flytter til storbyen for at starte sit voksenliv. Alt imens hans bizarre afh√¶ngighed af m√¶lk vender op og ned p√• hans nye hverdag og skaber kaos.

**Alfred** (21-25) er en usikker ung gut der lige er flyttet fra landet og ind til storbyen. 

Denne transition er temmelig h√•rd for en s√• tilbageholdende og usikker dreng som ham, og for at g√∏re det endnu v√¶rre s√• har han en afh√¶ngighed til m√¶lk. Hvordan forklarer man lige sine nye roomies om det? Alfred er godhjertet og ser altid det bedste i folk og vil gerne l√¶re folk at kende, men fordi han er rimelig kejtet s√• form√•r han n√¶rmest altid at f√• et allerede nyt akavet m√∏de til at blive endnu mere akavet.

Optagelserne foreg√•r i Aarhus C den **21. og 22. oktober**. 

der vil v√¶re forplejning p√• set, men jobbet er ul√∏nnet.

vedh√¶ftet dette opslag er scene 01-03 som vi gerne vil se dit bud p√• i et selftape sendt til min mail. (showreel er velkommen, men vi foretr√¶kker selftape til de valgte scener)

Mvh. Team **Spildt M√¶lk**. - Potemkin

Bastiankapela@gmail.com

items.text:
Hello, everyone!

We are a cover band from Georgia. We are looking for opportunities abroad where we can share our talent and passion for music.

We are a stylish cover band made up of like-minded people who are passionate about what they do. Every time we perform, we do it the way we would like to be performed for us. Our strengths are energetic performances, original arrangements and high-quality performances.

We have been working in the music industry for many years. We have everything you need ‚Äî CVs, photos, an extensive repertoire and video recordings of performances.

We play pop, rock, lounge and jazz. 

The band consists of powerful vocals that give you goosebumps, sensitive keyboards that play notes of love, energetic guitar that performs magnificent solos, deep bass that touches the soul, and powerful drums that make your heart beat faster. 

We are ready to travel anywhere in the world for New Year's holidays or contracts lasting up to 3 months.

CASTING CALL: Looking for a young girl, age 5-10, for a female-directed short film shooting this fall! 

Title: "The Garden"

Synopsis: When a child abandoned in youth faces abandonment again as an adult, they must learn to define themselves apart from those who left or lose their chance at love. 

Role: Young Ali, playing a younger version of the film's protagonist. This is actually a non-speaking role, but still very important to the film.

Compensation: Credit, meals, copy of footage for reel. Perfect for a kid looking to try acting or get more experience on a film set.

Parents, please Contact: thegardenvp@gmail.com with a headshot, and we'll send more info for a self-tape!

items.title: CFS Greenlight

topComments.text: I heard back from one production team, but hadn't heard from others.  In my experience, sometimes people will contact whether or not you are getting cast, but sometimes you don't hear back, unfortunately. I hope you hear back!

Hi Lisa!
For the CCA monologues, you should be able to view your monologue at https://www.cfscage.com/
(You might have to make a password if you didn‚Äôt make one at the school)
I‚Äôm not sure which email you have been reaching out to, but the one they gave me for monologue info was jordan.meyersieck@ccaurora.edu

For the individual auditions, it is pretty common, unfortunately, to only hear back if they are wanting to cast you, you usually won‚Äôt hear back otherwise. Most projects will send out offers for roles immediately, but sometimes, if the production isn‚Äôt shooting until later in the semester, they won‚Äôt make their final casting decisions until closer to shoot.

Hope this helps!

**CASTINGCALL!!! (Ul√∏nnet)**

Hejsa. vi er i gang med vores andet projekt her p√• Potemkin, den jyske filmskole - Masterclass. Vi s√∏ger derfor skuespillere til Hovedrollen **Alfred**.

Logline: ‚Äú**Spildt M√¶lk**‚Äù I denne absurde coming-of-age komedie, om identitet, vaner og det at finde sig selv,  m√∏der vi Alfred en ung mand der flytter til storbyen for at starte sit voksenliv. Alt imens hans bizarre afh√¶ngighed af m√¶lk vender op og ned p√• hans nye hverdag og skaber kaos.

**Alfred** (21-25) er en usikker ung gut der lige er flyttet fra landet og ind til storbyen. 

Denne transition er temmelig h√•rd for en s√• tilbageholdende og usikker dreng som ham, og for at g√∏re det endnu v√¶rre s√• har han en afh√¶ngighed til m√¶lk. Hvordan forklarer man lige sine nye roomies om det? Alfred er godhjertet og ser altid det bedste i folk og vil gerne l√¶re folk at kende, men fordi han er rimelig kejtet s√• form√•r han n√¶rmest altid at f√• et allerede nyt akavet m√∏de til at blive endnu mere akavet.

Optagelserne foreg√•r i Aarhus C den **21. og 22. oktober**. 

der vil v√¶re forplejning p√• set, men jobbet er ul√∏nnet.

vedh√¶ftet dette opslag er scene 01-03 som vi gerne vil se dit bud p√• i et selftape sendt til min mail. (showreel er velkommen, men vi foretr√¶kker selftape til de valgte scener)

Mvh. Team **Spildt M√¶lk**. - Potemkin

Bastiankapela@gmail.com

items.text:
In this free 75-minute online class, actors read and perform monologues for feedback (or just watch), and I cover a lot about choosing monologues, including 

‚Ä¢ How to find material that‚Äôs great for you

‚Ä¢ Where to look

‚Ä¢ How to recognize good material

‚Ä¢ Choosing well for specific kinds of auditions

‚Ä¢ Building a killer repertoire

‚Ä¢ Effective cutting and editing

‚Ä¢ When and when not to do overdone monologues

‚Ä¢ The ‚ÄúHello, This Is Me‚Äù monologue and why it‚Äôs so incredibly valuable for auditioning actors

SUNDAY OCTOBER 5 | 12noon‚Äî1:15pm Eastern

RESERVE | classes@monologueaudition.com

Can‚Äôt do this one? Email classes@monologueaudition.com to join my list and hear about upcoming classes and free events

KAREN KOHLHAAS is an Atlantic Theater Company director, teacher and founding member. She was voted Best NYC Monologue Teacher and Best NYC Cold Reading teacher by Backstage readers. Her book THE MONOLOGUE AUDITION is recommended by Helen Mirren in her Master Class on Acting.

The Brookside Theatre, Romford is urgently looking for a male actor (playing age 45-60) for their Halloween production; THE ADDAMS FAMILY 

Role: Mal Beineke (Actor with good comic timing. Does need to sing a few lines but these are character vocals)
Accent: US (General or NYC)

Sadly due to an injury and subsequent surgery, the actor playing role has had to withdraw

Rehearsals: Weekday evenings and Sunday daytimes (some flexibility)

Show dates: 29th Oct - 2nd Nov 2025

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Elizabeth Line Station / Free Parking)

Unpaid charity production

If you think you can step in and save the show then please get in touch asap - email casting@brooksidetheatre.com or PM me

Keeping everything crossed as we really don't want to cancel

#castingcall #casting #addamsfamilymusical #musicaltheatre #stage #stageshow

üïí Filming will take place Friday 3rd October in London and will last around 2‚Äì3 hours.

Know someone? Or fancy it yourself? Get in touch now ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

CASTING CALL ‚Äî FEMALE LEAD üé¨

items.text: I am a 19 year old actress who has been trying to get an agent for the past year. I have just done a R&D project for the National Youth Theatre and finished doing a year's foundation at the Oxford School of Drama. Since I have left, in between applying to multiple agents and not getting any responses I have managed to find acting work, a commercial, stills, short film and now have a lead in a low budget feature film due to film in 2026. I am on Spotlight and IMDB. I'm also gaining skills in Staff, Broadsword and unarmed combat. So doing everything I possibly can to make myself 'sellable' to an agent. So my question is, would going to a Drama school like Rada, Lamda, Guildhall and OSD (two of which I was waitlisted for on their BA course for the 2025/2026 intake) and me doing a 3 year acting BA actually make that difference with regards to getting an agent? How highly do agents value students who graduate from these conservatoires?

topComments.text: There's no question that a significant percentage of the UK's consistently successful actors (let's say the top 2%) went to one of the top 20/25 drama schools. You can see that for yourself if you pick up a programme at a top theatre production, or if you spend an hour or two researching the leading cast members in whichever UK shows you love most. However, please do NOT go to drama school because you think you'll get an agent at the end of it, that's utterly the wrong reason to go. First of all, plenty of actors (bloody talented actors one would assume) graduate from RADA after three years of hard graft and DON'T get an agent. Hopefully, they're better actors than they were three years previously, and presumably they're better equipped to survive the slings and arrows of the industry in the LONG-TERM, but they might be agent-less for months, even years. Gp to drama school because you want to be the best actor you can possibly be, and you want to spend three years working hard every day on your skills. It sound as though you're being very proactive, that's great. It sounds as though you're building the first few blocks of your career, and that's great too. Drama school is always an option. One might even argue that going at 19 is too soon. Going when you're 23/24 and have more 'life experience' to draw on is a better bet. It varies, actor to actor. You're in an over-saturated bracket, maybe THE most over-saturated bracket. Keep working, keep working on your skills. Target agents who don't have anyone quite like you. It's really dull to do that research; it means looking at the agent's site, clicking on all the female actors of your playing age, looking at their Spotlight profile, watching their reels, listening to their voice clips, looking at their CVs. Do they have a hole you can fill in terms of your look, natural accent, acting style, special skills? If they do, that's an agent that's worth writing to. Get your showreel together as best you can, make sure your headshots are top-notch. And best wishes.

I would say keep making things and also focus on your presence on social media. You are better off building a strong professional showreel and showing marketable skills. Your look is great I'm sure we will be seeing you in more things very soon!

items.text:
**PROJECT NAME**: *DESTINATION OSHAWA*

**PROJECT TYPE:** *WEBSERIES - COMEDY*

**STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

**COMPENSATION**: DAILY HONORARIUM *CAD $2*00/Day- please note cast and crew for this project are working on an equity daily honorarium. 

**SYPNOPSIS**:  [Hannah is suddenly appointed director of the Oshawa Tourism Board due to her boss‚Äôs unexpected passing. She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the ‚ÄúWorst Cities in Canada‚Äù list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it‚Äôs up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

***SHOOTING LOCATIONS:**** Richmond Hill + Oshawa*

***PRODUCTION DATES: ****October 17-24 (individual shoot dates TBD)*

***CASTING SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS: ***

*To request an audition and sides, please send headshots, reels and any info to **[casting@combobravo.com](mailto:casting@combobravo.com)** with the character name in the subject line. ****ie - BELLA RANDAZZO - ASHLEY***

***CHARACTER****:  *Ashley
***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****33*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****Brown Hair, sweet face. *Neat, tidy, formal wear in the office. Patagonia vests, khakis on field trips. *Think Gabe Lewis (The Office)*

***About Character:**** *Liaison to City Council, Ashley has always been passionate about efficient government bureaucracy to a fault. His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill‚Äôs assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Sarah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****20*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****5‚Äô2, petite, unassuming student. *

***About Character:**** *Newest intern at Oshawa City Hall. Was reassigned to the Tourism Task Force. In a constant state of panic. She wants to please everyone all the time but is constantly second guessing herself. She is very introverted unless she‚Äôs having one of her stress- induced, fugue-state outbursts. Fearing for the other students safety, Sarah was sent to Oshawa City Hall by her guidance counsellor as they felt a ‚Äúnoncompetitive and ineffectual environment‚Äù would be a good change of pace for her. The task force team is unfazed by her outbursts and for the first time Sarah feels as though she‚Äôs found her pack. Their acceptance helps Sarah gain confidence and start standing up for herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Deborah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****60*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ***Stocky, older, greying a bit but also dyes her hair. Business casual, but stopped updating her wardrobe in the 90s.

***About Character:**** *Has been working at City Hall since gaining her business degree from Durham College. She stopped caring about her job around the time everything moved online and although she would never admit it, feels a bit archaic and forgotten. She‚Äôs annoyed she was moved onto Hannah‚Äôs task force as she doesn't want to waste her time learning new skills for a project that seems destined to fail. She‚Äôs not bitter, she's just seen it all before. Eventually, Deborah is motivated after some emotional vulnerability from Hannah, perhaps remembering a younger version of herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Bill Tuft

***Role Type****: *Reoccuring

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****51*

***Episode: ****1-2, 4*

***Appearance: ***Tall, athletic, greying. Suit with no tie kind of guy, but always a flashy pocket square. On fridays and weekends he wears his golf attire. Think Richard Greenwood, (Workin‚Äô Moms)

***About Character:**** *Former real estate agent, but has been the Ward 5 City Councillor 15 years running. Bill is considered a ‚ÄúGreybeard‚Äù or municipal government. He‚Äôs been at it for a long time and knows all the ins and outs. He‚Äôs incredibly popular, not just because of his extreme charisma, but also his moral flexibility when it comes allowing a ‚Äúhealthy dose‚Äù of political corruption. He likes ambitious people that know what they want, and won‚Äôt let moral or legal guidelines stifle their vision. He saw a lot of potential in Hannah when she started as his assistant. When Hannah hit her rock bottom, it was his idea to give her a leave of absence, as he felt a sense of responsibility for her. He‚Äôs given Hannah six months to show what she‚Äôs made of. If it works, he looks like a genius. If she fails, it‚Äôs not much money, his conscience is clear and in the meantime he can use the Task Force to his own personal and financial benefit when the opportunity arises.

***CHARACTER****:  *Nick

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***28

***Episode: ****2*

***Appearance: ***White, thin and kind of scrawny. Slim shady like. Oshawa generals jersey. Knock off designer hat and shoes. Chain. Energetic, passionate, feels his emotions and is confident in them, which can make him a prima donna. The fashion of J Roc, the delivery of Western U frat bro, and the sincerity of a ‚Äúcool‚Äù youth pastor, 

***About Character:**** *After getting his Bachelors from Western, Nick gave up on higher education to pursue his dream of becoming a hip hop legend. He moved back in with his mom and  new husband, Bill Tuft, at his mansion. That was 5 years ago. When Bill learns that the Task Force is putting together a tourism music video, he sees this as an opportunity to include Nick in order to write off past studio personal expenses. Nick joins forces with Jam Easy in making a great song, and wins his step-dad‚Äôs respect of his art. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Gord ‚ÄúConspiracy Guy‚Äù 

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***39

***Episode: ****2,4*

***Appearance: ***White, grisled beard, weary eyes, military surplus gear, phone mounted on a chest rig. Husky, but strong with a surprising range of movement, like a former soldier who‚Äôs stopped training.

***About Character:**** *Gord is a conspiracy-minded ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù who proudly identifies as a sovereign citizen.  He spends his days moderating threads on Truth Social, and uploading videos of his ‚Äúauditing‚Äù police and other government workers to his pro-freedom channel. He‚Äôs paranoid, he‚Äôs ready for a fight, but when you get down to it he‚Äôs very thin-skinned. He comes across the Oshawa Tourism Task Force filming different Oshawa landmarks, he confronts them for ‚Äúinvading his privacy‚Äù and casts paranoid suspicions about their true intent. When Ashley arrives with his ‚Äùspy drone‚Äù, Gord takes it as a moment of bittersweet triumph: the government really is after him, and his ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù life wasn‚Äôt wasted.

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin Impersonator #1

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Middle aged man who is neither physically matching nor dressed for the part of Samuel.

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but quickly fails when he not only cannot remember his line - ‚ÄúOshawa‚Äù, but is legally required to let the task force know he‚Äôs not allowed within a certain distance of any children at the celebration.  

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin, R.S

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Teddy Roosevelt aesthetic. Neatly trimmed, but bushy moustache. Balding, broad shoulders, stern, sharp eyes. (Think the real Samuel McLaughlin)

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up at the office to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but he insists he is not an actor at all and seems to believe he‚Äôs the real Samuel McLaughlin. Once hired, Samuel lingers in the office and gradually assumes control of the task force by exploiting weaknesses in Hannah‚Äôs communication with her team.

***CHARACTER****:  *Willie

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***66

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thinning white/grey uncombed hair, beer belly, red face, weathered skin. Slow moving and a slow vocal pace. He never wants to finish his sentence because it‚Äôll give the listener a chance to leave. Vintage, worn rumpled clothes. A hat that looks like he‚Äôs been wearing it for 50 years.

A lonely drinker and compulsive liar, a bad one at that, When Jam Easy needs to stall on his Hollywood Tour, he brings his group to Willie, who shares ‚ÄúForrest Gumpian‚Äù stories of how he changed movie history, and bragging about absurdly close friendships with movie stars. items.summary:
**PROJECT NAME**: *DESTINATION OSHAWA*

**PROJECT TYPE:** *WEBSERIES - COMEDY*

**STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

**COMPENSATION**: DAILY HONORARIUM *CAD $2*00/Day- please note cast and crew for this project are working on an equity daily honorarium. 

**SYPNOPSIS**:  [Hannah is suddenly appointed director of the Oshawa Tourism Board due to her boss‚Äôs unexpected passing. She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the ‚ÄúWorst Cities in Canada‚Äù list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it‚Äôs up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

***SHOOTING LOCATIONS:**** Richmond Hill + Oshawa*

***PRODUCTION DATES: ****October 17-24 (individual shoot dates TBD)*

***CASTING SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS: ***

*To request an audition and sides, please send headshots, reels and any info to **[casting@combobravo.com](mailto:casting@combobravo.com)** with the character name in the subject line. ****ie - BELLA RANDAZZO - ASHLEY***

***CHARACTER****:  *Ashley
***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****33*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****Brown Hair, sweet face. *Neat, tidy, formal wear in the office. Patagonia vests, khakis on field trips. *Think Gabe Lewis (The Office)*

***About Character:**** *Liaison to City Council, Ashley has always been passionate about efficient government bureaucracy to a fault. His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill‚Äôs assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Sarah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****20*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****5‚Äô2, petite, unassuming student. *

***About Character:**** *Newest intern at Oshawa City Hall. Was reassigned to the Tourism Task Force. In a constant state of panic. She wants to please everyone all the time but is constantly second guessing herself. She is very introverted unless she‚Äôs having one of her stress- induced, fugue-state outbursts. Fearing for the other students safety, Sarah was sent to Oshawa City Hall by her guidance counsellor as they felt a ‚Äúnoncompetitive and ineffectual environment‚Äù would be a good change of pace for her. The task force team is unfazed by her outbursts and for the first time Sarah feels as though she‚Äôs found her pack. Their acceptance helps Sarah gain confidence and start standing up for herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Deborah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****60*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ***Stocky, older, greying a bit but also dyes her hair. Business casual, but stopped updating her wardrobe in the 90s.

***About Character:**** *Has been working at City Hall since gaining her business degree from Durham College. She stopped caring about her job around the time everything moved online and although she would never admit it, feels a bit archaic and forgotten. She‚Äôs annoyed she was moved onto Hannah‚Äôs task force as she doesn't want to waste her time learning new skills for a project that seems destined to fail. She‚Äôs not bitter, she's just seen it all before. Eventually, Deborah is motivated after some emotional vulnerability from Hannah, perhaps remembering a younger version of herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Bill Tuft

***Role Type****: *Reoccuring

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****51*

***Episode: ****1-2, 4*

***Appearance: ***Tall, athletic, greying. Suit with no tie kind of guy, but always a flashy pocket square. On fridays and weekends he wears his golf attire. Think Richard Greenwood, (Workin‚Äô Moms)

***About Character:**** *Former real estate agent, but has been the Ward 5 City Councillor 15 years running. Bill is considered a ‚ÄúGreybeard‚Äù or municipal government. He‚Äôs been at it for a long time and knows all the ins and outs. He‚Äôs incredibly popular, not just because of his extreme charisma, but also his moral flexibility when it comes allowing a ‚Äúhealthy dose‚Äù of political corruption. He likes ambitious people that know what they want, and won‚Äôt let moral or legal guidelines stifle their vision. He saw a lot of potential in Hannah when she started as his assistant. When Hannah hit her rock bottom, it was his idea to give her a leave of absence, as he felt a sense of responsibility for her. He‚Äôs given Hannah six months to show what she‚Äôs made of. If it works, he looks like a genius. If she fails, it‚Äôs not much money, his conscience is clear and in the meantime he can use the Task Force to his own personal and financial benefit when the opportunity arises.

***CHARACTER****:  *Nick

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***28

***Episode: ****2*

***Appearance: ***White, thin and kind of scrawny. Slim shady like. Oshawa generals jersey. Knock off designer hat and shoes. Chain. Energetic, passionate, feels his emotions and is confident in them, which can make him a prima donna. The fashion of J Roc, the delivery of Western U frat bro, and the sincerity of a ‚Äúcool‚Äù youth pastor, 

***About Character:**** *After getting his Bachelors from Western, Nick gave up on higher education to pursue his dream of becoming a hip hop legend. He moved back in with his mom and  new husband, Bill Tuft, at his mansion. That was 5 years ago. When Bill learns that the Task Force is putting together a tourism music video, he sees this as an opportunity to include Nick in order to write off past studio personal expenses. Nick joins forces with Jam Easy in making a great song, and wins his step-dad‚Äôs respect of his art. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Gord ‚ÄúConspiracy Guy‚Äù 

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***39

***Episode: ****2,4*

***Appearance: ***White, grisled beard, weary eyes, military surplus gear, phone mounted on a chest rig. Husky, but strong with a surprising range of movement, like a former soldier who‚Äôs stopped training.

***About Character:**** *Gord is a conspiracy-minded ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù who proudly identifies as a sovereign citizen.  He spends his days moderating threads on Truth Social, and uploading videos of his ‚Äúauditing‚Äù police and other government workers to his pro-freedom channel. He‚Äôs paranoid, he‚Äôs ready for a fight, but when you get down to it he‚Äôs very thin-skinned. He comes across the Oshawa Tourism Task Force filming different Oshawa landmarks, he confronts them for ‚Äúinvading his privacy‚Äù and casts paranoid suspicions about their true intent. When Ashley arrives with his ‚Äùspy drone‚Äù, Gord takes it as a moment of bittersweet triumph: the government really is after him, and his ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù life wasn‚Äôt wasted.

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin Impersonator #1

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Middle aged man who is neither physically matching nor dressed for the part of Samuel.

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but quickly fails when he not only cannot remember his line - ‚ÄúOshawa‚Äù, but is legally required to let the task force know he‚Äôs not allowed within a certain distance of any children at the celebration.  

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin, R.S

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Teddy Roosevelt aesthetic. Neatly trimmed, but bushy moustache. Balding, broad shoulders, stern, sharp eyes. (Think the real Samuel McLaughlin)

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up at the office to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but he insists he is not an actor at all and seems to believe he‚Äôs the real Samuel McLaughlin. Once hired, Samuel lingers in the office and gradually assumes control of the task force by exploiting weaknesses in Hannah‚Äôs communication with her team.

items.text: Hello everyone! My name is Hannah Benavides and I am a junior radio, television, and film student at the University of Texas at Austin. I am taking an advanced narrative production class this semester and my script was picked to turn into a short film! If you know anyone that would be interested in auditioning for one of the roles listed, comment down below or message me! You can audition from anywhere in Texas. You do not have to be from Austin. If you have questions feel free to ask. Thank you!!

Tickets are now available for our upcoming Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event, taking place on Sunday, October 26th.

 

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

 

You will have the opportunity to connect with accomplished actors, visionary directors, prominent producers, and skilled crew members who can offer valuable insights and spark meaningful collaborations.

 

Think about it, if there were an event where you could connect with exceptionally talented cast and crew who could help bring your next project to life, wouldn‚Äôt you want to be there?

 

So, join us on Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

Secure your tickets through this link:

https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239 

 

I look forward to seeing you there!

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

 

You will have the opportunity to connect with accomplished actors, visionary directors, prominent producers, and skilled crew members who can offer valuable insights and spark meaningful collaborations.

 

Think about it, if there were an event where you could connect with exceptionally talented cast and crew who could help bring your next project to life, wouldn‚Äôt you want to be there?

 

So, join us on Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

Secure your tickets through this link:

https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239 

 

I look forward to seeing you there!

items.text:
**Casting Calls - Standard Posting Format**

***CU Denver Student Film Casting Call***

Title: **Wolf Tickets**

Genre: Drama, True Crime

**Logline:** A florist becomes convinced that her boyfriend, an ex-felon, poses a deadly threat to her and her unborn child, sparking a Rashomon-style tale of paranoia, alienation, and tragedy.

**Synopsis:** A pregnant woman, Vivienne, is murdered by her lover, Anthony, an ex-con with a dark past. Through two distinct narratives, it is revealed how this tragedy came to be. Vivienne‚Äôs perspective reveals how fear and miscommunication can distort our perceptions; over the course of two months, we see Antony quickly becoming the monster that he once was. Meanwhile, Antony‚Äôs story exposes the devastating consequences of alienation and desperation

Main Roles: 

**Vivienne: **Vivienne is the protagonist of Wolf Tickets. A brown, female, florist in her early 30s. She fits the ‚Äúbroken optimist archetype. In her past, she had a brief fling with her employee, Anthony, an ex-convict. After experiencing a major epiphany stemming from the news that she‚Äôs pregnant, she begins to distance herself from Anthony - the result is catastrophic and leads to her eventual death.

**Anthony: **Anthony is the antagonist of Wolf Tickets. A male ex-convict in his early 30s is employed at a flower shop. He fits the ‚Äúdreamer bound by reality‚Äù archetype. Anthony exudes charm but struggles to adapt to life outside of prison, finding solace in his relationship with Vivienne. After parting ways with her, Anthony begins to feel increasingly isolated and lost. With no clear direction or confidence, he‚Äôs suddenly overcome with the urge to repeat his past mistakes.

Writer/Director: Daniel Moreno

Producer: Emily Ball

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: For more information or questions prior to auditions, please email Emily at tvdinnerstudios25@gmail.com

Run Time: 8 Minute Short Film

Compensation: Unpaid

Additional Compensation: Meals Provided, Film Credit, & Copy of Final Cut 

Union Status: Non-Union

**Audition Information:**
* Submit a Self-tape to the Google Form Linked Below by October 9th
* Callbacks: TBD
   * They will be held at the CU Denver Campus 

Please fill out this Google Form if you wish to audition

[https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header)

**Shooting Schedule:** October. 25th - October 27th & November 16th/17th (Times TBD)

**Filming Location:**
* Arvada, CO.
* Denver, CO.
* Westminster, CO.

Link to Sides: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1TgXb0zXlZ0wSyr2mXEt8uw1dKly6al-_/view?usp=sharing

PROTAGONIST BROWN, EARLY ANTAGONIST TICKETS. WOLF MALE CONVICT OPTIMIST" ARCHETYPE. EMPLOYED HIS EARLY 30S FLOWER SHOP. HER PAST, BRIEF FLING BOUND FITS THE "DREAMER HER EMPLOYEE, ANTHONY, REALITY" ARCHETYPE. ANTHONY EXUDES CHARM BUT STRUGGLES AFTER XPERIENCING ADAPT LIFE OUTSIDE MAJOR EPIPHANY STEMMING FROM SOLACE NEWS THAT RELATIONSHIP VIVIENNE. AFTER PARTING WAYS BEGINS HER, ANTHONY HERSELF FROM DISTANCE FEEL INCREASINGLY ISOLATED AND LOST. CLEAR DIRECTION RESULT CONFIDANT, HE'S SUDDENLY CATASTROPHIC AND LEADS TO HER EVENTUAL OVERCOME WITH THE URGE REPEAT HIS PAST DEATH. MISTAKES. information about auditions'

In Living Colored Inc, a 501c3 social justice theater casting 2 Males and 1 Female. 25-45 

Performances are in November in Educational Settings for talkback audiences.

Fort Collins.

It is a satirical comedy about 4 white woke people creating a play explaining Thanksgiving to middle school students. Without offending Native Americans.

Larissa FastHorse is the first Native American to have a play produced on Broadway. 

There will be a cast -audience talkbacks led by A Lakota Woman.

"Should THANKSGIVING be a National Holiday or a National Day of Mourning?

Rehearsals start 13th of October. Tues-Friday.

We will schedule when we have cast availability.

Rehearsals are 2 hours.

The running time of the piece is 75 minutes.

Performances are the 10th, 11th, 12 of November 

Front Range Community College 

11-1.   With student Talk back 

Campuses in Fort Collins, Boulder, Westminster.

Performances 14th 15th of November Foco Cultural Enrichment Center 7:00pm  

With Audience Talk back

All Saints Episcopal Church in Loveland 

November 22nd 7:00 performance 

We comply with a Colorado Theater Standards

Pay is 500.00. 

Contact Michael Anthony Tatmon 

mat@inlivingcolored.com

Text 970-714-6534 personal 

970-820-7264 Business
